Introduction

TAN (Korean: 탄; Japanese: タン), which stands for To All Nation, was a seven-member project boy group signed under Think Entertainment.

The group was formed through the survival show Wild Idol and consists of idols who already made their debut in the industry such as 24K's Changsun, We In the Zone's Jooan, Trei's Jaejun, Rainz' Sanghyuk, and NTX's Jiseong. Members Taehoon and Hyunyeop were the only members who didn't have prior idol experience.

TAN made their official debut on March 10th, 2022, with their first mini-album '1TAN'.

On June 29, 2024, Changsun announced on the group's official fan cafe that the group had disbanded and he is stepping down as leader as he leaves the idol industry.
